\backslash
beta|)^{2b+1}}.
 
\backslash
end{eqnarray} % We take the parameter $b=2$, and the GPD in the zero skewness
 case is defined according to the {
\backslash
it ansatz}, $H_{q/
\backslash
pi}(
\backslash
beta,0,t) = H_{q/
\backslash
pi}(
\backslash
beta,0,0)
\backslash
, F_
\backslash
